HEADWORD: Suctorian
<hw>Suc*to"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A cartilaginous fish with a mouth adapted for
suction, as the lampery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the Suctoria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suctorious</ent>⟦br⟧
